- 22:06 GMT - USA
The city of Chicago reimposed some coronavirus [COVID-19] restrictions on Monday [20 Jul 2020] and the state of Florida reported more than 10 000 new cases for the 6th day in a row, as the coronavirus pandemic raged across the United States. New York state recorded only 8 deaths on Sunday [19 Jul 2020] while the total number of people hospitalised for the disease fell to 716, the fewest since [18 Mar 2020], Governor Andrew Cuomo said. But metrics for the country as a whole have grown worse. 32 states have reported record increases in COVID-19 cases in July [2020] while 15 states have reported record increases in deaths. Deaths, hospitalisations, and rates of positive test results continue to climb with at least 15 states reporting record hospitalisations so far in July [2020], according to a Reuters tally. [Apparently New York City has had outdoor partiers on the weekends, non-masked, not observing social distancing. It would not be surprising if the daily cases starts increasing in New York City, as the virus is still present. As for elsewhere, the Southeast of the USA is experiencing major surges in cases (see section [3] [E] below.) - Mod.MPP

HealthMap/ProMED map of the United States: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7595820,106]

- 20:25 GMT - Saudi Arabia Hajj
This year's [2020] hajj, which has been scaled back dramatically to include only around 1000 Muslim pilgrims due to the coronavirus pandemic, will begin on [29 Jul 2020], Saudi authorities said Monday [20 Jul 2020]. "The stand of pilgrims on Mount Arafat, the peak of the hajj ritual, falls on Thursday [30 Jul 2020]," the official Saudi Press Agency. [In a prior post, the Saudi specified the Hajj attendees would be a "very limited number of participants from various nationalities already present in Saudi Arabia." (see COVID-19 update (282): Saudi Arabia hajj, hindsight, WHO, global 20200624.7504138) - Mod.MPP

HealthMap/ProMED map of Saudi Arabia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7595820,131]

- 19:00 GMT - Spain
The prevalence of coronavirus in Spain has risen 3-fold over the last 3 weeks as authorities struggle to contain a rash of fresh clusters, mainly in the Catalonia and Aragon regions, Health Ministry data showed on Monday [20 Jul 2020]. After registering thousands of cases and hundreds of deaths per day during an early April [2020] peak, Spain succeeded in slowing the number of new infections to a trickle. But since restrictions on movement were lifted and Spaniards relaxed back into daily life, some 201 new clusters have appeared, with heavy concentrations in and around the Catalan cities of Barcelona and Lleida. The occurrence of the novel coronavirus has jumped from 8 cases per 100 000 inhabitants at the end of June [2020], when the country's state of emergency ended, to 27 per 100 000, deputy health emergency chief Maria Sierra told a news conference on Monday [20 Jul 2020]. "Where measures have been relaxed is where these clusters appear," Health Minister Salvador Illa said. "We're talking about gatherings of extended family and spaces associated with nightlife" [Another country experiencing major increases in transmission after lifting restrictions. - Mod.MPP

HealthMap/ProMED map of Spain: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7595820,43]

- 16:30 GMT - Bahamas introduces restrictions as cases rise
Bahamas will shut its borders to international flights and commercial vessels carrying passengers, the country's prime minister said. Flights from the UK, Canada, and EU countries are exempted, Hubert Minnis said. The restrictions will come into effect on Wednesday [22 Jul 2020]. Bahamas has reported 153 cases and 11 deaths, according to a tally by Johns Hopkins University. [Hmmm, exempting high incidence COVID-19 countries... - Mod.MPP

