- 15:45 GMT - Indigenous people
Indigenous communities comprising half a million people around the world are especially vulnerable to the new coronavirus pandemic due to often poor living conditions, the World Health Organization (WHO) warned. Director General Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus said that as of [6 Jul 2020], there were more than 70 000 cases reported among indigenous peoples in the Americas, with over 2000 deaths [see WHO situation report section [4] below, and COVID-19 update (193): global, China, CFRs, Amazon Indigenous pop, WHO 20200519.7352326 for more background. - Mod.MPP

- 09:42 GMT - Indonesia
Indonesia reported its 2nd-highest daily increase in coronavirus-related deaths with 96 fatalities, a day after registering a record daily jump in deaths, data presented by health ministry official Achmad Yurianto showed. The country also reported 1693 new infections, taking the total to 88 214, the highest number in East or Southeast Asia, with a total of 4239 deaths. [Indonesia has been reporting in the 1200-1500 range daily newly confirmed cases since 23 Jun 2020. - Mod.MPP

