[There were 11 new confirmed cases in the past 24 hours; 3 were imported, and 8 were locally acquired -- 7 in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region and 1 in Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps. This brings the tally of this new cluster up to 58 cases -- not counting asymptomatic infections. According to a media report, a 2nd city is now involved to the southwest of Urumqi - Kashgar (Xinjiang https://en.brinkwire.com/us/fresh-outbreak-in-xinjiang-spreads-to-a-second-city-as-hong-kong-faces-out-of-control-surge/). It is now 15 days with no new cases reported from Beijing.

There were 6 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals (1 imported) and 1 new conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, China has reported 39 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infection.

Hong Kong reported 73 new cases. The official government site in Hong Kong mentions a total of 1958 cases (confirmed) and 1 probable. The newly reported cases announced today (20 Jul 2020) involve 31 males and 42 females aged between 4 and 94 years. Among them, 7 had travel history during the incubation period, 8 were asymptomatic. (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/20/P2020072000862.htm). Travel history was the Philippines (1), Japan/South Korea (1), South Korea (1), Kazakhstan (1), Ethiopia (1), and Qatar (1). (https://gia.info.gov.hk/general/202007/20/P2020072000862_346159_1_1595259445402.pdf)

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2 and has occasional cluster flair-ups (see comments in the section on South Korea below). Hong Kong is dealing with increased local transmission associated with the lifting of restrictions; new severe restrictions have been announced. Cases are primarily locally transmitted although there are importations.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7595820,155. - Mod.MPP]

