Cases still continue to be concentrated in Lombardy, Veneto and Emilia-Romagna, the main provinces at the original epicenter of the outbreak (see tables at the link on the source URL. The provinces reporting the largest numbers of newly confirmed cases in the 24-hour period are Lombardy (56), Emilia-Romagna (42), and Veneto (42), Lazio (14), and Liguria (12), are the provinces reporting 10 or more cases. A total of 16 provinces reported fewer than 10 newly confirmed cases (9 provinces reported no new cases). Italy is now 75 days post phase 2 initial opening up and 59 days post 2nd stage of phase 2 opening up. More detailed information on the outbreak is available at http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=english&id=5367&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto.

Interpretation: So far so good, but there are periodic signs of localized increased transmission. Time will tell.

