In a press briefing on Monday [20 Jul 2020], Sima-Sadat Lari said 217 people have also died of the virus in the past 24 hours, bringing the total number of fatalities to 14 405. She confirmed 2414 new cases of infection with the novel coronavirus, raising the total number of cases to 276 202 [this count differs with our count (276 070) but multiple sources give this so an adjustment must have been made by the government. - Mod.MPP]

3583 patients are also in severe condition of the disease, she added. Lari noted that 2 175 217 COVID-19 tests have been taken across the country. She said there has been no change in the list of "red" and "orange" zones of COVID-19 risk in the country, urging people to wear face masks, observe social distancing and health protocols.

